Edo Council of the Nigeria Union of Journalists has lauded the passage of the bill establishing the Federal College of Education in Ekiadolor, Benin. The bill which was sponsored by the Chairman, Senate Public Accounts Committee, Senator Mathew Urhoghide, was passed by the Senate on Tuesday. Senator Urhoghide, representing Edo South Senatorial district, was equally lauded by the Edo NUJ for a job well done. In a statement signed by the Chairman of the NUJ, Mr Festus Alenkhe, the union described the passage of the bill as a positive development with multiplier effects on the government and people of the state. The union noted that with the passage of the bill, teachersâ€™ education in the state would receive a boost. It added that the bill, now awaiting presidential assent would boost the socio-economic activities of the Ekiadolor community and its environs when it becomes a law. NAN